pr-worktree [PR_NUMBER | JIRA_KEY | --suffix SUFFIX | -s SUFFIX]

Pick a GitHub PR or JIRA issue via fzf and create a sibling git
worktree for it. With no argument, an fzf picker is shown listing,
in this order:

  1. GitHub PRs in the current repo that involve you (opened,
     commented, reviewed, assigned, mentioned).
  2. JIRA issues that matter to you, served off the shared
     ~/.cache/rlm-jira/items.tsv cache (assigned -> reporter ->
     watching -> DATA-only, with previously-picked tickets floating
     to the top via the shared MRU history at
     ~/.cache/rlm-jira/history.txt). The cache is populated on the
     first call to either rlm-pr-worktree or rlm-jira-pick; to force
     a refresh, run rlm-jira-pick and pick the REFRESH sentinel.
     Skipped silently if acli is missing or unauthenticated.
  3. Other open PRs in the repo that don't involve you, so you can
     pick up a teammate's PR for local review.

Selecting a PR creates a worktree at  ../<repo>-pr-<N>  on the PR
branch. Selecting a JIRA issue first prompts (vared, editable) for
an optional free-form suffix:

  - Empty input: worktree  ../<repo>-<KEY>  on a new branch named
    <KEY>/feat/<key_lowercased>  off origin/<default-branch>, e.g.
    DATA-1234 -> branch DATA-1234/feat/data_1234. The branch always
    follows the project-wide <KEY>/feat/<slug> convention.
  - A non-empty value like "fix bq cost" becomes a path slug and a
    branch slug: worktree  ../<repo>-<KEY>-fix-bq-cost  on a new
    branch named  <KEY>/feat/fix_bq_cost  off the same base. Runs
    of non-alphanumerics collapse to a single separator; the path
    uses '-' and the branch slug uses '_' so the result matches the
    project-wide  <KEY>/feat/<snake_case>  branch convention.

When called with an argument, the picker is skipped:
  - A numeric value is treated as a PR number.
  - A value matching the JIRA key shape (e.g. DATA-1234) is treated
    as a JIRA issue; the same suffix prompt is shown.
  - --suffix SUFFIX (or -s SUFFIX) creates a worktree at
    ../<repo>-<SUFFIX> on a new branch named <SUFFIX> off
    origin/<default-branch>, with no PR or JIRA lookup and no
    prompt — handy for scripts.

If the target worktree path already exists, it is entered instead of
recreated.

Requires: gh, git, fzf. acli is optional (enables the JIRA rows).
